features: Experience Unparalleled Freedom: Say goodbye to tangled cords and embrace the ultimate convenience of the Lenovo 510 Wireless Keyboard and Mouse combo. This powerful duo operates seamlessly using a single 2.4 GHz nano-USB receiver, streamlining your workspace, and liberating your ports.

Elegance Redefined: Elevate your desk aesthetic with the Lenovo 510's sleek wireless design. Its minimalistic charm adds a touch of sophistication to any workspace. Enjoy the ease of use that requires no complex installations – simply plug in and go.

Uncompromised Durability: Accidental spills are no longer a threat with the spill-resistant wireless keyboard of the Lenovo 510. Its intelligent island design and comfortable keys on the full-size layout ensure effortless typing, even in the face of minor mishaps.

Effortless Comfort, Any Hand: Designed for extended usage, the ambidextrous and ergonomic 1200 DPI wireless mouse is the perfect companion for both left and right-handed users. Revel in the convenience of a 12-month battery life powered by a single AA battery.

Enhanced Efficiency: Never struggle with password errors again, thanks to the LED indicators on the Caps Lock and Num Lock keys. Stay on top of your input with these user-friendly visual cues, streamlining your tasks and enhancing your overall computing experience.
body.description: Rediscover the joy of typing on a full-size tilting computer keyboard with the Lenovo 510. Wave goodbye to clutter and tangled cords as you immerse yourself in a spacious, unobstructed workspace. The keyboard's water-resistant casing ensures durability and resilience against unexpected spills. Engage in precise pointing and control with the wireless mouse that accompanies the Lenovo 510. Designed to cater to both left and right-handed users, its ambidextrous layout guarantees ergonomic comfort. With a 1200 DPI optical sensor, every movement is accurate and responsive, enhancing your productivity. With a remarkable battery life of up to 12 months on just a single AA battery, you can bid farewell to the inconvenience of constantly replacing batteries and say hello to a cord-free lifestyle. Please note that battery life may vary based on individual usage patterns.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 8, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Superb quality and endurance — tested for a year before posting review. Survived water damage too!
reviews.reviewText: This is my first Amazon review, and I did use this keyboard a year first before posting the review for a holistic, time-tested experience. The mouse and keyboard are very durable and of excellent quality. I purchased in 6/14 and today is 7/8 — which means I have experienced 0 problems and a happy year of dependable, efficient usage.The keyboard is very energy efficient and uses 2 AAA batteries. It’s been a year now but I don’t think I’ve changed the battery yet in the keyboard yet.The mouse has gone through 2 battery replacements. But because I use computer for work, school, heavy coding, gaming, and artistic projects, it’s to be expected. The mouse also glows in a tiny orange light when it’s 5-7 days away from needing a replacement so you can know in advance and not face a sudden dead-battery incident. (I have gone through days of gaming with that little orange light and the mouse still works and delivers) It is pretty unbelievably good for the $30 I’ve paid on this set.SURVIVED COFFEE ATTACK from Cat Knockover.Cats, am I right? I work, take classes, and teach classes, at home and my feline buddies are a constant variable in my life. A week ago, one knock over my coffee ( Large size - Hot ) when I went on a 5min bathroom break. I came back fully expecting the keyboard not to work. But once I wiped it down, I’m very pleasantly surprised and relieved that I can still work. Half of the keyboard was completely soaked by sweet brown coffee but seems fine. . . ? I’ve gone a week since and there were no key failures. The quality endures!Some keys were sticky, like Crtl, Fn, Shift and so forth. I was planning to buy a new one but decided to try cleaning the sticky ones with some cotton balls, tissue, and rubbing alcohol. Works like a charm and now I DONT NEED TO Buy a new keyboard!Super good quality and it does survive liquid accidents. :) Take that, Cat!Buy this! I’m legit too happy, especially since it’s gone $2 cheaper than a year ago.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars After four month: Mouse broken, keyboard defect!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this combo in May 2023. Some weeks later the prints of numbers and letters started to fade. Some letters are not readable anymore in September. But it comes worse. I needed to change three times the batteries in the keyboard. But sometimes the keystrokes produces ten times the same letter, even I only pressed the key one time. Just a week ago, the mouse started to open and close websites, I did not even click on. And often, when I click a link or a buttom the mouse does not react at all. Buttom line is. This product is in my personal perception absolute garbage. However, I had Microsoft and Logitech keyboards before, who also only lived one year. But within four month only this Lenovo combo died. Remarkable. Today, I will order a Cherry keyboard combo. Let's see how that works out.
